/u/luddyjun on Changing behaviors may be easier when people see norms changing - "In a study, people ate less meat and conserved more water when they thought those behaviors reflected how society is changing."
Comparing vegetarianism and veganism to being a fad is making the whole movement a disservice. A large part of it is for ethical reasons. Saying that people are doing it just because it's the in thing is a very incorrect line of thinking in my opinion.   